# Status reporting (mandatory)

After EVERY completed task, milestone, ADR, migration, feature, refactor, or
architecture change, produce BOTH:

1. **Status document** — create/update `docs/status/YYYY-MM-DD-task-name.md`
   following `docs/status/TEMPLATE.md`.
2. **Canvas artifact** — create/update the canonical project-state canvas
   (`project-state.canvas.tsx` in the workspace canvases directory,
   `~/.cursor/projects/<workspace>/canvases/`). The Canvas is the canonical
   project state document.

The Canvas must contain: Objective, Scope, What was implemented, Files added,
Files modified, Architectural decisions, Deviations from plan, Risks, Test
results, Acceptance status, Next recommended step.

Assume a new engineer joins tomorrow and only reads the latest Canvas — they
must understand the current state without reading git history or previous
chats.

The chat summary stays short; the detailed explanation belongs in the Canvas
and the status document. Never deliver implementation results as chat text
only.
